\begin_layout Abstract(en)
In the field of computer vision, the goal of most research about human faces
 is to identify, include face detection, recognition, alignment.
 As most of existing approaches and databases are limited to 2D images,
 it is difficult to fully reflect the facial features, which causes the
 limitation of face recognition.
 3D face model is expected to provide more information to break through.
 However, as exiting 3D face databases can not provide enough models and
 facial expressions, and some of which lack key parts like ears or chin,
 it is important to produce a more complete 3D face database.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Abstract(en)
This paper aims to build a 3D face capture and reconstruction system, which
 can provide multiple face images with various expressions and directions
 under multiple lightings.
 There are three parts as follows:
\end_layout

