\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
\paragraph_spacing other 1.5
Build a multi-camera, light controllable system and design the supporting
 synchronous capture software.
 This system includes ten high resolution color cameras and two Kinect2
 depth cameras.
 Light sources include four professional photography lights with uniform
 illumination and 120 individually controllable LED lights, which can achieve
 multi-direction synchronous capture under different lights.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
\paragraph_spacing other 1.5
Build a simple multi-camera capture system, using six synchronized photoflash
 and ten SLR camera to get high-quality images.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
\paragraph_spacing other 1.5
Build a cylinder GoPro camera array, and design the supporting camera control
 software.
\begin_inset VSpace -30bp
\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
\paragraph_spacing other 1.5
Present a novel calibration device and algorithm, which can calibrate multiple
 cameras of different scales and FOVs.
 Compared with traditional methods like chessboard or one dimensional balls,
 this solution is much simpler, faster and more accurate.
 This calibration algorithm not only suits for this hardware system, but
 also works for other multi-camera systems, especially for cameras of different
 scales.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
\paragraph_spacing other 1.5
The core of this paper is 3D face reconstruction algorithm.
 This method first calculates the disparity map according to pixel matching
 of images, then reconstructs high quality 3d face cloud robustly, and after
 some postprocessing, finally produces textured mesh model.
 This method can also be used for 3D reconstruction of other objects and
 is expected to play a role in other fields like historical relic reconstruction.
\end_layout

